The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 February is 38,659 (4,474.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 February, there were 1,265 new confirmed cases (146.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 February, there were 1,930 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 34% (665 fewer cases).
